# nbdev Workflow

## Source of Truth

- **Notebooks in `nbs/` are the source of truth.** All code lives there.
- **NEVER edit `.py` files in `{{MODULE_NAME}}/` directly.** They are auto-generated by `nbdev-export` from notebooks. Any manual edits will be overwritten.
- To change exported code: edit the notebook cell with `#|export`, then run `nbdev-export`.

## Export Directives

- `#|default_exp module_name` — top of notebook, declares target module
- `#|export` — cell exports to the Python module
- `#|hide` — cell runs but is hidden from docs
- `#|eval: false` — cell is not executed during `nbdev-test`
- No directive — cell appears in docs but is not exported (good for demos/tests)

## What to Export

Export functions that are: reused across notebooks, well-tested, conceptually complete.
Do NOT export: one-off exploration, ad-hoc inspection, debugging cells, prototypes.

## Commands

- `nbdev-export` — export notebooks to `.py` modules (run frequently during dev)
- `nbdev-test` — run all notebook cells as tests
- `nbdev-prepare` — export + test + clean (run before every commit)

## Autoreload

Notebooks that import and call library functions (orchestrators, dev notebooks, exploratory work) use autoreload at the top:
```python
%load_ext autoreload
%autoreload 2
```
Library notebooks that *define* exported code do NOT need this.
